{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "POS Tagging"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Part-of-speech (POS) tagging assigns a grammatical label — noun, verb, adjective, preposition, and so on — to every token in a sentence. The labels come from a standardised tagset; the most widely used in English NLP is the Penn Treebank tagset with 36 tags."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Three-panel diagram: (top) POS tags on 'The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog'; (middle) dependency parse arcs with labels det/nsubj/prep/pobj; (bottom) constituency parse tree showing S → NP + VP."}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "POS tags are an intermediate representation used by almost every downstream NLP component: parsers consume them, NER systems use them as features, and rule-based extractors rely on them to match patterns like \"adjective followed by noun.\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Penn Treebank tags"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tag"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "NN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Noun, singular"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "dog, model"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "NNS"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Noun, plural"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "dogs, models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "VB/VBZ/VBD/VBN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Verb base / 3sg-present / past / past-participle"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "run / runs / ran / run"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "JJ"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adjective"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "quick, large"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "DT"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Determiner"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "the, a, an"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "IN"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Preposition or subordinating conjunction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "in, over, because"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "PRP"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Personal pronoun"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "I, he, she, they"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "RB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Adverb"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "quickly, very"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "POS Tagging with spaCy"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "spaCy's pipeline runs tokenisation, POS tagging, and dependency parsing in one call. Each "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "Token"}, {"type": "text", "text": " object exposes both the coarse Universal Dependencies tag ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pos_"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") and the fine-grained Penn tag ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "tag_"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install spacy && python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm\nimport spacy\n\nnlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\ndoc = nlp(\"The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.\")\n\nfor token in doc:\n    print(f\"{token.text:<12} {token.pos_:<8} {token.tag_:<6} {token.dep_}\")"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "The          DET      DT     det"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "quick        ADJ      JJ     amod"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "brown        ADJ      JJ     amod"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "fox          NOUN     NN     nsubj"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "jumps        VERB     VBZ    ROOT"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "over         ADP      IN     prep"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "the          DET      DT     det"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "lazy         ADJ      JJ     amod"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dog          NOUN     NN     pobj"}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dependency Parsing"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dependency parsing builds a directed tree where each arc connects a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "head"}, {"type": "text", "text": " word to a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "dependent"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and is labelled with the grammatical relation (subject, object, modifier, etc.). The root of the tree is the main verb. Every sentence has exactly one root."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dependency relations from the Universal Dependencies standard that appear most often:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "nsubj"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — nominal subject: the noun phrase that performs the action."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "dobj"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — direct object: the entity acted upon."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "amod"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — adjectival modifier."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "det"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — determiner (the, a)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "prep"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — prepositional modifier."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "pobj"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — object of a preposition."}]}]}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import spacy\n\nnlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\ndoc = nlp(\"Apple acquired Shazam in 2018.\")\n\n# Extract subject–verb–object triples\nfor token in doc:\n    if token.dep_ == \"ROOT\":          # main verb\n        subj = [c for c in token.lefts  if c.dep_ in (\"nsubj\", \"nsubjpass\")]\n        obj  = [c for c in token.rights if c.dep_ in (\"dobj\", \"attr\")]\n        if subj and obj:\n            print(f\"({subj[0].text}, {token.text}, {obj[0].text})\")\n# → (Apple, acquired, Shazam)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This subject–verb–object extraction pattern is the foundation of simple relation extraction and knowledge graph construction pipelines."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Constituency Parsing"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Constituency parsing groups tokens into nested "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "phrases"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — noun phrases (NP), verb phrases (VP), prepositional phrases (PP) — and arranges them in a tree rooted at S (Sentence). Each internal node is a phrase type; leaf nodes are words."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The NLTK toolkit provides a simple constituency parser via the Stanford Parser or the built-in Earley chart parser:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import nltk\nfrom nltk import CFG, ChartParser\n\n# A tiny hand-written grammar to illustrate the concept\ngrammar = CFG.fromstring(\"\"\"\n  S   -> NP VP\n  NP  -> DT JJ NN | DT NN\n  VP  -> VBZ PP\n  PP  -> IN NP\n  DT  -> 'The' | 'the'\n  JJ  -> 'quick' | 'lazy'\n  NN  -> 'fox' | 'dog'\n  VBZ -> 'jumps'\n  IN  -> 'over'\n\"\"\")\n\nparser   = ChartParser(grammar)\nsentence = ['The', 'quick', 'fox', 'jumps', 'over', 'the', 'lazy', 'dog']\n\nfor tree in parser.parse(sentence):\n    tree.pretty_print()\n    break"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For production use with full English coverage, the Berkeley Neural Parser ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "benepar"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") integrates directly with spaCy:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install benepar && python -m spacy download en_core_web_md\nimport spacy, benepar\n\nbenepar.download(\"benepar_en3\")\nnlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_md\")\nnlp.add_pipe(\"benepar\", config={\"model\": \"benepar_en3\"})\n\ndoc  = nlp(\"The quick fox jumps over the lazy dog.\")\nsent = list(doc.sents)[0]\nprint(sent._.parse_string)\n# (S (NP (DT The) (JJ quick) (NN fox))\n#    (VP (VBZ jumps)\n#        (PP (IN over)\n#            (NP (DT the) (JJ lazy) (NN dog)))))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dependency vs. Constituency Parsing"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dependency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Constituency"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Structure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Word-to-word arcs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Nested phrase spans"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Relation extraction, SVO triples, semantic role labeling"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Grammar-checking, machine translation alignment, parsing ambiguity"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Faster (linear or near-linear)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slower (cubic CYK; neural benepar is fast)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-lingual transfer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strong (Universal Dependencies covers 100+ languages)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Weaker (phrasal structures are more language-specific)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Practical Applications"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NER feature engineering"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": POS context around a candidate span (is it a noun? preceded by a determiner?) improves entity detection."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule-based information extraction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": match patterns like VERB → dobj → NOUN to extract actions, or ADJ → amod → NN to extract properties."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Coreference resolution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": POS tags identify pronouns; dependency trees show which noun phrase a pronoun modifies."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Question answering"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": constituency spans map directly to candidate answer spans in reading-comprehension systems."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Grammar and style checking"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": detect passive voice (VBN with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "auxpass"}, {"type": "text", "text": " dependency), dangling modifiers, and run-on sentences."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluation"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "POS tagging accuracy is measured as the fraction of tokens with the correct tag. State-of-the-art neural taggers (fine-tuned BERT) reach ~98 % on the Penn Treebank. On out-of-domain text accuracy drops to ~93–95 %."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Dependency parsing uses two metrics:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "UAS (Unlabelled Attachment Score)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": fraction of tokens whose head is correctly identified."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "LAS (Labelled Attachment Score)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": fraction of tokens whose head AND dependency label are both correct. Always LAS ≤ UAS."}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "spaCy's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "en_core_web_trf"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (RoBERTa-based) achieves UAS ≈ 95 % and LAS ≈ 93 % on the OntoNotes benchmark."}]}]}}